Tank = Ability to take damage and keep the mobs taunted on you.<br>
Melee = Ability to do damage using weapons<br>
<br>
Below level 40 all tanks and melees are nearly the same, Warrior, Ranger, Monk, Rogue, Pally, Sk, even Bard at taking damage if they are wearing banded/ bronze or better. To take the needed damage BETTER you add more Ac, more Ac and 3rdly more HP Items. If you notice that one tank is much better at taking damage, you'll find out that this person is a Twink and has better than avg. AC + HP for his level, Twinks are out there and just because they seem better than you doesn't hurt you any. When I was new and a low level, I loved grouping with Twinks, most twinks know small things from high levels that make camps and fights go ALOT more smoothly, most will have some basic knowledge on how to play that class, most take much less loot and items from the group (they have no need for FS weapons and bronze, they only want lots of exp fast and not to die). After about lvl40, Warriors start to gain an increased edge in Tanking (AC, from higher defence and better items. HP bonuses are widening the gap above other classes) and the further in levels they go the more the margin is increased.<br>
<br>
EQ Rumor: 2handed weapons do more damage than duel weld FALSE unless compared to 2 much weaker 1handers.<br>
<br>
Fact: Big 2handers only LOOK like they do more damage. what catches your eye are the BIG hits that make you say Wow, but what your not thinking about all the smaller hits and misses that they are getting with these slow 2handers.<br>
<br>
How damage works: All melee classes get a damage bonus based on level and on weapon damage/ delay in their PRIMARY hand and, many believe, a much smaller bonus on off-hand. Slower Delay 2handers do have an increased damage bonus, <br>
<br>
Example1: With the same Str and similar Dam/ Del Ratios (discounting the proc):<br>
<br>
Oggok Cleaver: ( 44 DMG 60 DLY 15 WT) Max Damage 249<br>
<br>
Zealots Incarnadine Sword: ( 26 DMG 35 DLY +5 DEX, EFF: SOUL BOND) Max Damage 147<br>
<br>
Poison Wind Censer: ( 20 DMG 28 DLY 5 WT, +5 STR, -30 SV POISON, EFF: GALE OF POISON) Max Damage 113<br>
<br>
Of those three examples many are suprised to know that the Poison Wind Censer will do more damage consistantly than the other two (twice as many swings and since, more swings = more hits = more times the bonus is added), even though the Oggok cleaver will look like your doing a ton more with it's big hits. A Weapon's damage tends to fall closer to the median of all hits, than their max damage suggests. Exception to this is when higher end Haste is added to these weapons, slow weapons get more of a Haste bonus than faster weapons.<br>
<br>
Example2: before being nerfed Moss Covered Twig 3/10 and a Barbscale Whip 4/11 being duel welded was the best weapon combination a warrior could use, they did VASTLY more damage than ANY other weapon combo in the game. This combo was so powerful that they nerfed them and their use is only Avg. now.<br>
<br>
The reason that the Twig and Whip we so powerful is because of the sheer number of extra swings that you get at such low delay, and with every hit the damage bonus is added. These weapons relied on only the damage bonus to do damage, as their base damage is minor.<br>
<br>
Strength is also of questionable means to increase damage (shock, suprise, alarm), Shaman have lately been testing the effects of Strengh on general melee damage. From my understanding of reading alot of posts on the subject, Higher Strength = Higher Max Damage, but a higher strength (boosted by Spells or Item stats) has a much smaller effect on median damage (where a majority of all your hits fall) and the increase seems to be based on the Attack increase gained from the Str boost. Median Damage is based on weapon based damage (regarless of str) and attack stat. Spells (Boon of Garou, Fire fist, Pet buffs, Wolf form) and Items (Lupine Dagger)with Attack+ seem to have more effect on increase damage output than just raising your Attack with a Strengh buff.<br>
<br>
Another issue to consider when picking weapons is Taunt Factor, Warriors usually being the main tank, want to keep the mob hitting them and need to build up mob hate. Mobs currently seem to count Misses as equal to a Hit when calculating Hate. Many Warrior's choose duel welding fast weapons (Faster = More Swings {Hits AND Misses}) when Main Tanking to increase the effectiveness of Taunt and use a big 2hander at other times when they are back-up tank. This effect can be noticed in the amount of Hate a Ranger/ Monk/ Rogue builds up while duel welding the fast weapons common to those classes. Weapon proc will also add Hate.<br>
<br>
People study alot of things to decide what weapons, armor, classes to use. The main thing to remember is this is a game and to have fun.<br>
<br>
I currently think that if your under lvl 35 the difference between a Mithril Imbrued Longsword and Yak and Cane of the Tranquil or a Runic Caver and Exe Axe and Mithril Staff are not very noticable and not worth much time concerning yourself over. If you spend your time hunting wisely you'll be higher level in no time and you'll have more money and be looking for a different class of weapon soon enough.<br>
<br>
Bria, here is a short list of good weapons that are under or about 1000pp, all are about 3x better than what I had when, lvl 20 and until I looted an Iksar Berzerker Club at lvl 29 and a GJB at lvl 40+/-<br>
<br>
Ebon Razor<br>
Crystallized Sword (off-hand)<br>
Nathsar Greatsword<br>
Runic Carver 200-300pp!<br>
Blackjack<br>
Wraithbone Hammer<br>
Harpoon of the Depths<br>
Obsidian Shard Proc!<br>
Dragoon Dirk 50pp!<br>
Mithril Staff <br>
Ketchata Koro Mis delay30 50pp!<br>
Abandoned Orc Shovel delay27 (Lake Rathetear at the Orc Camp) Free!<br>
<br>
I'd suggest keeping one sword and getting a decent/ fast 1blunt, piercing, 2slash, 2blunt, 2piercing and use these to keep ALL your weapon skills maxed. Having those skills maxed will serve you well in the later game when many of the nicer weapons that you may loot or need are of all different types (Jade Mace, Blood Point, Felhammer, etc.), get ones with low delay so you'll have faster skill increases. I know a lvl 52 Pally that, will remain nameless, can't use her, Darkmetal Holy Water Sprinkler, a sweet mace that she looted in Plane of Hate because she never worked on her Skillz at lower levels, and it is too hard to raise them later. :P<br>
